http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/%E2%80%98Govt.-taking-measures-to-provide-quality-medicare%E2%80%99/article13998631.ece

Minister for Finance and Civil Supplies Etala Rajender said the State government was taking all measures to provide quality medicare to patients in all government hospitals on par with the corporate hospitals.Speaking during the Mothers’ Day programme held at the government headquarters hospital here on Wednesday, the Minister said that the programme was aimed at encouraging deliveries in government hospitals.Stating that more than 80 per cent deliveries were taking place in private hospitals, he said the latter were conducting 90 per cent caesarean sections burdening the patients.A total of 52,000 to 55,000 deliveries take place every year in the district of which only 12,000 take place in government hospitals.He said the government was taking all measures to completely equip the hospitals. He asked people not to approach private hospitals and incur loss on deliveries. On this occasion, he also launched a vehicle meant to provide free transportation for women after delivery.DM&HO Md Aleem said the Mothers’ Day programme was aimed at providing medical assistance to women in their seventh month or more and to make them approach PHCs for normal delivery and area hospitals for caesarean sections.The authorities have set a target of performing at least 2,000 deliveries a month in government hospitals.Zilla Parishad Chairperson Tula Uma, MLC Naradasu Laxman Rao, Mayor S. Ravinder Singh, Collector Neetu Prasad and others were also present.Minister for Finance and Civil Supplies Etala Rajender participates in Mothers’ Day programme